DocAssociado: IPECO Service Bulletin (SB) 063-25-08/  IPECO Service Bulletin (SB) SB 063-25-09  IPECO Service Bulletin (SB) SB 063-25-10   IPECO SB 063-25-14.
Assunto: ATA 25 – Equipment / Furnishings – Pilot and Co-pilot Seats – Modification /Inspection
Justificativa: Assentos instalados na aeronave PR-MPW são pós mod 08670 (ATR SB 25-1157/IPECO SB 063-25-14)- prosseguir conforme abaixo    1) Dentro de 750 FH- inspecionar todas as molas afetadas de cada assento afetado de acordo com as instruções do Boletim de Inspeção (IPECO SB 063-25-14);    2) Se- durante qualquer inspeção requerida no item 1)- algum dano ou incorreta instalação de cada mola afetada (Identificada conforme Boletim de Inspeção) for encontrada. Antes do próximo vôom substitua ambas as molas de acordo com as instruções do boletim de inspeção.    Credito para assentos instalados em aeronaves ATR: Se- durante alguma inspeção requerida no item 1) dessa diretriz- algum dano ou instalação incorreta de apenas uma mola afetada (Conforme identificada no Boletim de Inspeção) for encontrada em um dos assentos (Piloto ou Co-piloto)- é permitido deferir o cumprimento das ações corretivas requeridas no item 2) por até 10 dias calendaricos desde que uma cópia do ATR Operations Engineering Bulletin (OEB) "Untimely Pilot Seat Unlocking" esteja inclusa no AFM- pilotos estejam informados e a aeronave esteja operado conforme o OEB.      -  Instalação de Peças:  A partir da data efetiva desde diretriz- é permitido instalar um assento afetado em uma aeronave desde que- antes da instalação-  o assento foi inspecionado (Sem defeitos encontrados) de acordo com as instruções do Boletim de Inspeção e que- conforme a instalação- o mesmo esteja sendo inspecionado conforme item 1);    A partir da data efetiva da diretriz- é permitida a instalação de molas afetadas em um assento instalado em uma aeronave desde que- antes do próximo vôo após a instalação- a mola passou por uma inspeção (Sem defeitos encontrados) de acordo com as instruções do Boletim de Inespeção e que a mesma seja inspecionada conforme item 1) posteriormente.

Justificativa: Modification :  (1) Within 12 months after 14 december 2018- modify each affected part in accordance with the instructions of the SB EBAT72    - For the aircraft listed on the applicability list of this technical documentation analysis- no action is required because they have not embodied the modifications listed on appendix  1 of the airworthiness directive    Parts Instalation  (2)  After modification of aircraft as required by paragraph (1) of this analysis do not instal an affected part on that aircraft    - No action is required for the aircraft listed on the applicability list because the paragraph (1) of this analysis is not applicable

Assunto: Global Navigation Satellite System - Operational Limitations
Justificativa: Use of Navigation Database   (1) Within 30 days after the effective date of this AD- update the aircraft's navigation database where all RNP-AR procedures within SBAS areas and certain LPV procedures- as listed in the SIL- have been removed and- thereafter- use only a regularly updated navigation database where the above-mentioned procedures are not included.  - For the aircraft mentioned on the applicability list of this analysis- no action is required because it is not equiped with thales Topstar 200 LPV GPS/SBAS receiver  AFM UPDATE  (2) For the ATR72-212A equipped with ATR MOD 7180- MOD 7182 or MOD 7585  in production or on wich SB ATR72-34-1143 or ATR72-34-1145 or SB ATR72-34-1154 has been embodied in service : Within 30 days after the effective date of this AD- amend Section 1.2 "Each Flight Checks" of the applicable AFM by inserting the AFM change as defined in this AD- inform all flight crew and- thereafter- operate the aeroplane accordingly.   - For the aircraft mentioned on the applicability list of this analysis- no action is required because it is not equiped with modification quoted on paragraph 2 of this analisys.  (3) After amending the AFM of an aeroplane- as required by paragraph (2) of this analysis- introducing a later approved ATR AFM Revision that contains the AFM Change- as defined in this AD- into the applicable AFM is an acceptable method to comply with the requirements of paragraph (2) of this analysis   -No action is required for this paragraph because paragraph (2) is not applicable for the aircraft listed on the applicability field of this analysis

Assunto: ATA 32 - Landing Gear - Main Landing Gear Bush - Inspection
Justificativa: - INSPECTION(S):    1) Inspect the bush P/N D61002 intallation of LH and RH MLG in accordance with the instructions of the AOM;    - CORRECTIVE ACTION(S):    2) If- during the inspection as required by paragraph (1) of this FADT- the bush is found in wrong position as defined in the AOM- before next flight- remove the affected MLG- and replace it with a serviceable MLG- as defined in this FADT- in accordance with the instructions of the AOM.    - PARTS INSTALLATION/LIFE LIMIT IMPLEMENTATION:    3) For serviceable MLG- Scenario 1: Within 12 months or 3000FC- wichever occurs first since (re-)installation on an aeroplane as required by paragraph (2) of this AD- replace it with a serviceable MLG- as defined in this AD- in accordance with the instructions of the AOM    4) From the effective date of this AD- each MLG removal and installation must be accomplished in accordance with the instructions of the JIC 321100 RAI 10000 (Dated 09/07/2019) (Ref to AOM 2019/12);    CREDIT:    5) Inspection and- depending on findings- correction of an aeroplane- accomplished before the effective date of this AD in accordance with the instructions of ATR AOM 2019/12 at issue 1- is an acceptable method to comply with the requirements of paragraphs  (1) and (2) of this AD for that aeroplane;    REPORTING    6) Within 30 days after the accomplishment of the inspection as required by paragraph (1) of this AD- or within 30 days after the effective date of this AD- wichever occurs later- report the inspection results (including no findings) to ATR. Using the instructions of the AOM is an acceptable method to comply with this reporting requirement.    NOTE:  Serviciable MLG:     - Scenario 1: Any MLG on which the bushing P/N D61002 was found wrongly installed and which was corrected in accordance with the AOM and has accumulated less than 12 months or 3000 FC since first re-installation after correction; or   - Scenario 2: An MLG on which the bushing PN D61002 was found correctly installed in accordance with the instructions of the AOM;

Assunto: ATA 92 - Engine Nacelle Electrical Wiring/ATA 29 - Underwing Box Hydraulic Pipe
column21: Modification:      (1) Within 24 MO or 5000 FH whichever occurs first after effective date-modify the electrical wiring routing installation on both engine nacelles IAW applicable SB;      On the date of this analysis- MSN 682 accumulated TSN 25876-28 & CSN 38795   Inspection(s):     (2) Before next flight after the required modification- accomplish a DVI of the propeller brake hydraulic pipe for chafing with the screw head on RH underwing box of the engine nacelle- IAW the AOM;  Corrective Action(s):     (3) If- during the inspection as required by paragraph (2) of this AD- the hydraulic pipe is found damaged- before next flight replace the hydraulic pipe with a new one IAW the AOM;      (4) If- during the inspection as required by paragraph (2) of this AD- the gap between hydraulic pipe and screw if found to be less than 6mm- before next flight- contact ATR for approved repair instructions and- within the compliance time(s) specified therein- accomplish those instructions accordingly.

Assunto: Fuselage - Passenger Seat Tracks - Inspection/Repair/Replacement
column21: NOTE: Accomplish within 26 months after 18/05/2020 (Effective date of the original issue)  Perform a GVI to confirm if the aircraft has an affected part installed.   Affected part: A seat track having Part Number (P/N) S53570203200- P/N S53570203202- P/N S53375001212- P/N S53375001213 or P/N S53375001214 and manufactured between year 2012 and year 2017 inclusive- or a seat track having a P/N as listed above- where the manufacturing batch number is not legible. The manufacturing date of the seat track can be identified by the batch number; an example is provided in Appendix 1 of this AD.  1) Inspection:   Accomplish a one-time DVI of each affected part IAW the applicable SB (ATR42-53-0151)  2) Corrective Action(s):  If- during DVI as requiredby par.(1)- deficiences are found- accomplish corrective actions IAW instructions of the applicable SB.   - Finding located at the level of at least one pax seat fitting: Perform corective ations before next flight;  - Finding not located at the level of at least one pax seat fitting: Within 24 months after the inspection as required or at next relocation/replacement of cabin seats (WOF).  3 - Parts Installation: From 18 May 2020- installation of an affected part is allowaed- provided that it is a serviceable part.

Assunto: Wings - Outer Wing Box Upper Rib Feet
Justificativa: On the date of this analisys- aircraft MSN 561 has already performed fisrt inspection on 22/12/2018 (IAW EASYFLY WO 37900 - MSN 561 has accumulated 50325-30 FH and 46080 Cy) Next accomplishment of the following inspection should be done at intervals no to exceed 48 months or 6000FC. On the date of this analysis aircraft has accumulated TSN: 51874-9 and CSN: 48295- next accomplshment should be done until 20/12/2022 or when achieves 52080Cy WOF.  Accomplish a DVI of the LH and RH wing rib upper feet and upper panel between rib 24 and rib 29 IAW instructions of ATR SB.  Contact ATR for approved repair instructions if any discrepancy is detected during any inspection required- before next flight- within the compliance time specified in those instructions.  Repair of an aeroplane- as required above- does not constitute terminating action for the repetitive DVI as required- unless the ATR repair instructions specify otherwise.  Within 30 days after each DVI as required- the repair instructions have to be sent to ATR IAW instructions of ATR SB.

Assunto: ATA 92 - Electronic Common Installation - Engine Nacelle Electrical Wiring - Modification
column21: Accomplishment should be done with 24 MO or 5000 FH after 26/11/2019 (In 26/11/2019 MSN 561 has accumulated TSN: 51.860-05).  Modification  (1) Modify the electrical wiring routing installation on both engine nacelles IAW instructions of the applicable SB;  Inspection  (2) Before next flight after the modification as required by paragraph (1) of this AD- accomplish a DVI of the propeller brake hydraulic pipe for chafing with the screw head on RH underwing box of the engine nacelle IAW instructions of the AOM;  Corrective Action(s):   (3) If- during the inspection as required by paragraph (2)- the hydraulic pipe is found damaged- before next flight- replace the hydraulic pipe with a new one IAW instructions of the AOM  (4) If - during the inspection as required by paragraph (2) of this AD- the gap between hydraulic pipe and screw is found to be less than 6mm- before next flight-contact ATR for approved repair instructions and- within the compliance time(s) specified therein- accomplish those instructions accordly.

Assunto: Pilot and Co-Pilot Seats - Modification/Inspection
column21: Last periodic inspection accomplished on Captain seat (LH) P/N 3A063-0079-02-4 (S/N: 25734) in 28/01/2020 IAW EASYFLY RW-708301 (Aircraft has accumulated 51862-72 FH).  Next accomplish should be done within 750FH after last inspection.  - Inspection:  Inspect any affected spring of each affected seat IAW the instructions of the inspection SB.  - Corrective action:  If- during any inspection as required- any damage or incorrect installation of an affected spring is found- before next flight- replace both springs IAW instructions of the inspection SB.  - Credit:  For affected seats- installed on ATR aeroplanes: If- during any inspection as required by paragraph (3) of this AD- any damage or incorrect installation of only one affected spring is found on the pilot or co-pilot seat- it´s allowed to defer accomplishment of the corrective actions as required by paragraph (4) of this AD for that seat by up to 10 calendar days- provied a copy of the ATR OEB. "Untimely Pilot Seat Unocking" is included in AFM- pilots are informed and aeroplance is operated IAW instructions of that OEB.  - Parts Installation:  It is allowed to install an affected seat on an aeroplane provided- before installation that seat passed an inspection (No defect found)- IAW instructions of the inspection SB and that- following installation- it is inspected as required.  From the effective date of this AD- it´s allowed to install an affected spring on a seat installed- on an aeroplane provided that- before next flight after installation- that spring passes an inspection (no defect found) IAW instruction of the inspection SB and that- thereafter- it is inspected as required.

Assunto: Fuselage – Passenger Seat Tracks – Inspection / Repair / Replacement
Justificativa: NOTE: Accomplish within 26 months after 18/05/2020 (Effective date of the original issue)  Perform a GVI to confirm if the aircraft has an affected part installed.   Affected part: A seat track having Part Number (P/N) S53570203200- P/N S53570203202- P/N S53375001212- P/N S53375001213 or P/N S53375001214 and manufactured between year 2012 and year 2017 inclusive- or a seat track having a P/N as listed above- where the manufacturing batch number is not legible. The manufacturing date of the seat track can be identified by the batch number; an example is provided in Appendix 1 of this AD.  1) Inspection:   Accomplish a one-time DVI of each affected part IAW the applicable SB (ATR72-53-1108)  2) Corrective Action(s):  If- during DVI as requiredby par.(1)- deficiences are found- accomplish corrective actions IAW instructions of the applicable SB.   - Finding located at the level of at least one pax seat fitting: Perform corective ations before next flight;  - Finding not located at the level of at least one pax seat fitting: Within 24 months after the inspection as required or at next relocation/replacement of cabin seats (WOF).  3 - Parts Installation: From 18 May 2020- installation of an affected part is allowaed- provided that it is a serviceable part.

The manufacturing date of the seat track can be identified by the batch number; an example is provided in Appendix 1 of this AD.  1) Inspection:   Accomplish a one-time DVI of each affected part IAW the applicable SB (ATR72-53-1108)  2) Corrective Action(s):  If- during DVI as requiredby par.(1)- deficiences are found- accomplish corrective actions IAW instructions of the applicable SB.   - Finding located at the level of at least one pax seat fitting: Perform corective ations before next flight;  - Finding not located at the level of at least one pax seat fitting: Within 24 months after the inspection as required or at next relocation/replacement of cabin seats (WOF).  3 - Parts Installation: From 18 May 2020- installation of an affected part is allowaed- provided that it is a serviceable part.
